# MCP servers are the keystone signal: their traffic routes through Anthropic's
# servers, so they bypass any VM network allowlist. A session that cannot fetch
# a live website may still create repos and deploy through MCP.
# The detector reports CONFIGURED only (parsed from .mcp.json / ~/.claude.json).
# It never claims authentication; the whereami skill verifies auth on demand
# with read-only calls and updates state.json.

Capability mcp.github
  Description GitHub MCP server configured (create repos, PRs, API without direct network)
  Probe mcp github
  Requires OAuth session on the Anthropic side
  Remediation Add the GitHub MCP server (claude mcp add, or a connector on claude.ai) and authenticate it once from an interactive session.
  Risk low
  Environments local cloud

Capability mcp.vercel
  Description Vercel MCP server configured (deploys without direct network)
  Probe mcp vercel
  Requires OAuth session on the Anthropic side
  Remediation Add the Vercel MCP server / connector and authenticate it once from an interactive session.
  Risk low
  Environments local cloud
